<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="052" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Default Playbook Seed — `Spaarke Assistant — General`</title>
    <phase>Phase 5: Surfaces + Templates</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>013, 025, 032</dependencies>
    <blocks>053, 054, 055</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, ai, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Data seeding + JSON authoring task; produces a new Dataverse record (`sprk_playbook`) consumed by all three starter Templates and the SpaarkeAi no-context landing. No new C# / TypeScript code; the deliverable is a JSON playbook definition + deploy invocation. Has explicit ADR constraints + dependencies (013, 025, 032).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Blocks tasks 053, 054, 055 (Templates seed against this default playbook). Single critical-path task within the Phase 5 Templates sub-group.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author and seed the `Spaarke Assistant — General` default playbook into Dataverse (`sprk_playbook` entity). This playbook is the configuration record that determines how the SpaarkeAi Code Page behaves at no-context landing: it sets the system prompt per design.md §7.4.3, registers the always-on tools (the 3 meta-tools `FindResources` / `GetResourceDetail` / `InvokeResource` from task 025 + the 3 foundational tools `SearchDocuments` / `QueryDataverse` / `GetCurrentEntityContext`), and points to `InteractiveInChatGateResolver` (task 032) as the default `IGateResolver` for any side-effect gates raised during conversational invocation. Per spec.md FR-13 + design.md §7.4.7, this single record is the configuration of the Assistant's default behavior — tuning is a Dataverse record change, not a code change.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke AI / JPS engineer with deep familiarity with the JPS Playbook entity schema (`sprk_playbook`), the `sprk_aichatcontextmap` lookup convention (how SpaarkeAi resolves the right playbook per surface context), and the playbook-seed deployment scripts in `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1`. You preserve idempotent seeding (re-running this task is safe).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **Playbook JSON definition** — `infra/insights/schemas/playbook-spaarke-assistant-general.json` containing the playbook record fields: `sprk_name`, `sprk_displayname`, `sprk_systemprompt` (the full §7.4.3 system prompt, verbatim), `sprk_alwaysontools` (JSON array of tool ids: meta-tools + foundational tools), `sprk_defaultgateresolver` (`InteractiveInChatGateResolver`), `sprk_modeltier` (`Standard`), `sprk_costbudget` + `sprk_latencybudget` (sensible defaults).
    2. **No-context aichatcontextmap entry** — a row in `sprk_aichatcontextmap` keyed by an empty/null entity logical name (the no-context default landing) pointing to this playbook. Other rows (entity-scoped) are added by future tasks; this is just the default.
    3. **Deployment** — run `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` (or the equivalent existing seed script — verify name via `Glob`) against the dev environment to upsert the record. Idempotent: re-running yields no diff.

    Deliverable: `infra/insights/schemas/playbook-spaarke-assistant-general.json`, a deploy invocation recorded in `notes/deploys/052-default-playbook-seed.md`, and a verification query confirming the record exists in Dataverse with the expected fields.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md FR-13 + Assumption "Default Assistant playbook ... provisioned via seed data on first deploy" + design.md §7.4.7 ("The Assistant default playbook is the configuration of all of the above") all point to a single Dataverse record carrying the Assistant's behavior. Design.md §7.4.3 specifies the verbatim system prompt — do NOT paraphrase; copy it exactly. Design.md §7.4.2 lists the always-on tools that bypass the `FindResources` hop for common requests.

      The playbook record is consumed by:
      - **SpaarkeAi Code Page** at no-context landing (task 050 parsing + task 052 lookup integration via `sprk_aichatcontextmap`)
      - **All three starter Templates** (tasks 053, 054, 055) inherit this playbook's system prompt + tool set unless they override
      - **The default `IGateResolver` routing** (task 032's `InteractiveInChatGateResolver`)

      The seed is **idempotent** — if the record already exists (e.g., from a previous run), the script upserts (update if present, insert if not). This is critical because Phase 6 deploys may re-run the seed and must not duplicate records.

      Per ADR-013 (refined 2026-05-20), this is BFF AI placement — the playbook record lives in Dataverse, consumed by BFF code via `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` facade where needed. No CRUD-side caller should query `sprk_playbook` directly.

      Per ADR-018, the playbook record's `sprk_featureflagref` field (if it exists in the schema) MUST reference a kill-switch flag (e.g., `feature.actionEngine.assistantDefault`) so the default playbook can be disabled without redeploying.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>infra/insights/schemas/playbook-spaarke-assistant-general.json</file>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/deploys/052-default-playbook-seed.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI placement: playbook record lives in Dataverse (system of record); BFF reads via `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` facade. No CRUD-side direct injection of `IPlaybookService` or playbook-internal types.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">Feature flag for opt-in: the default playbook MUST reference a feature flag / kill-switch (e.g., `feature.actionEngine.assistantDefault`) so it can be disabled per tenant / per environment without code changes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish size impact: this task adds NO BFF code — only Dataverse data + a JSON file under `infra/`. Publish-size delta is zero; no NuGet additions. Templates are JSON, low impact.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">System prompt MUST be copied verbatim from design.md §7.4.3 — do not paraphrase, rewrite, or condense. The prompt is the load-bearing discipline layer per design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #1.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Idempotent seed: re-running `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` MUST upsert (no duplicates). Verified by running it twice and checking record count = 1.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Always-on tools list MUST include exactly: `FindResources`, `GetResourceDetail`, `InvokeResource`, `SearchDocuments`, `QueryDataverse`, `GetCurrentEntityContext`. No more, no fewer in MVP.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Default `IGateResolver` MUST be `InteractiveInChatGateResolver` (the in-chat card per design.md §5). The other three resolvers are situation-specific opt-ins.</constraint>
  </constraints>

