  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`infra/insights/schemas/playbook-spaarke-assistant-general.json` exists and parses as valid JSON.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`sprk_systemprompt` field contains the verbatim text from design.md §7.4.3 (verified by string match — no paraphrasing).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`sprk_alwaysontools` array contains exactly 6 tool ids: `FindResources`, `GetResourceDetail`, `InvokeResource`, `SearchDocuments`, `QueryDataverse`, `GetCurrentEntityContext`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`sprk_defaultgateresolver` field value is `"InteractiveInChatGateResolver"`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`sprk_featureflagref` references a kill-switch flag per ADR-018.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">After deployment, exactly one `sprk_playbook` row with `sprk_name='spaarke-assistant-general'` exists in the dev environment.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">After deployment, exactly one `sprk_aichatcontextmap` row for the no-context default exists in the dev environment.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Re-running `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` does NOT create a duplicate record (idempotency verified).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta is zero (no BFF code change) — confirmed by `dotnet publish` comparison (or by inspection since this task adds no `.cs` / `.csproj` changes).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The system prompt in design.md §7.4.3 spans roughly 8 paragraphs. Copy it verbatim — including the bold emphasis, the "Based on general legal knowledge:" prefix instruction, and the "always offer 2-3 follow-up suggestions" closer. Paraphrasing weakens the discipline layer per guardrail #1.

    The `sprk_playbook` entity schema is created in task 013 (Foundation Phase). If a field name in this task does not match the schema (e.g., `sprk_alwaysontools` vs an actual `sprk_always_on_tools` column), defer to the actual schema from task 013 and document the mapping in `notes/deploys/052-default-playbook-seed.md`.

    The seed script name (`Deploy-Playbook.ps1`) is a best guess; verify via `Glob` in step 2. If the existing JPS deployment infrastructure uses `Deploy-JpsActions.ps1` or `Seed-Playbook.ps1` instead, use that — the skill workflow takes priority over the hardcoded name in this POML.

    Per spec.md "Assumptions" — default playbook provisioned via seed data on first deploy. This task IS that seed. Phase 6 deploys may re-invoke this task's deploy script (idempotency is critical).

    The `sprk_aichatcontextmap` row for the no-context landing has a NULL/empty `sprk_entitylogicalname`. Future tasks (post-MVP / R2) will add entity-scoped rows (e.g., `sprk_matter` → matter-specific playbook). This task only adds the default.
  </notes>

